We held a class here in the clinic on Thurs May 19. It was six diabetics some with high blood pressure. Five of the diabetics came with their wife or husband. We had actual food samples of what they could buy at the store, light foods, artificial sweetner drinks and condiments, fruits, vegetables....
We informed them of how important it is to take care of their skin and entire body. We gave them the packet we had been working on for a couple weeks. In it was the food/ meal plan schedule and exercise plan. the whole class was actually fun and most of all supportive because there was one patient that had been having trouble actually eating and had fallen into a deep depression after his diagnosis. Everyone showed their support by letting him know that all of them were going through it and what keeps them going is their family. At the end of the class everyone recieved a certificate.
